        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19241",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Internally, Zend_View simply uses include() to pull in a view script, after first resolving it to one of the paths in its internal stack. As such, it should be able to handle any of the URL fopen wrappers... but only if we support those for the registered paths. \n\nI see this as an edge case, however; most developers will be working with paths in the local filesystem and not require stream wrappers. Unless you're willing to provide a patch showing a proof-of-concept or the issue receives many votes, we likely will not implement it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-19T08:39:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-19T08:39:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19242",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Modified from bug to feature request.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-19T08:40:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-19T08:40:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19247",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lsaferite",
                        "name": "lsaferite",
                        "displayName": "Lee Saferite",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have to say that is a very disappointing response.  \n\nUsing any valid file path shouldn't be a feature request, it should be expected behavior.  If I can send it to the include function, then the internal Zend_View functions should handle it.\n\nI have patched Zend_View_Abstract to simply always use the unix style separator, as a simple stop-gap solution.  However, since it is not a 'real' solution I will not submit it as a patch.\n\nI stand by my earlier classification, this is a BUG not a feature request.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lsaferite",
                        "name": "lsaferite",
                        "displayName": "Lee Saferite",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-19T10:37:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-19T10:37:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19664",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Nobody else has commented on this issue, and there are no watchers or votes on it. I've seen no related bugs come through the issue tracker.\n\nFor the 1.6.0 release, I already have plans to modify Zend_View_Abstract to utilize Zend_Loader_PluginLoader and Zend_Filter_Inflector for resolving helper\/filter paths and classes -- primarily so that we do not have multiple solutions to a standard framework issue (plugins). This will likely resolve any issues you are seeing.\n\nI'm marking this as an *improvement*, not a bug, as you are not providing reproduce code and as the behaviour you're describing was never an intended behaviour of Zend_View.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-06T09:51:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-06T09:51:44.000+0000"
